What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: 20 hours of research is probably what you'll be spending in lab if you plan to do anything substantial at all, so I would recommend 495 to anyone who actually wants to have a legitimate project.

Great option to take if you want to be really devoted to a project. Not much direction from the class structure which leaves pretty much everything up to your PI. Get a PI you like and you'll be really happy you took this class.

I would recommend taking MCDB 495, especially if you are interested in doing research after graduation. Twenty hours in the lab is a lot of time but after my experience this semester, it's hard to imagine accomplishing too much with less time in the lab. I highly recommend it.
I would definitely recommend the class to anyone who is interested in research and wants to learn a lot about any area of interest.
